# Generated by Cargo
# will have compiled files and executables.
# `/target*/` covers the default `target/` plus the per-job target dirs the
# local CI script creates (`target-clippy/`, `target-test/`, `target-tarpaulin/`)
# so contributors running .github/scripts/local-ci.sh don't see them as
# untracked.
/target*/

# Remove Cargo.lock from gitignore if creating an executable, leave it for libraries
# More information here http://doc.crates.io/guide.html#cargotoml-vs-cargolock
# Cargo.lock

# These are backup files generated by rustfmt
**/*.rs.bk

# Example server
example/server/target

# Editor temp files
.vscode

# OS noise
.DS_Store
cobertura.xml

# Commit-hash stamp written transiently at `cargo publish` time so a crates.io
# install embeds the commit in `--version` (see CONTRIBUTING.md "Releasing").
# Force-staged for the publish only; never committed.
/git-hash
